04/08/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- General Burwell B. 
Bell, the commanding general of the US Army, Europe, arrived Tuesday (3 August) to attend the first joint Bulgarian-US military drill at the training range in Novo Selo. 
The drill, which began on 19 July, involves 900 US troops, 150 Bulgarian servicemen and 44 technical units. 
On Wednesday, journalists will visit the military camp and watch manoeuvres. 
(BNT, BNR, News.bg - 04/08/04)
